HEADWORD: Borecole
<hw>Bore"cole`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. D.
<ets>boerenkool</ets> (lit.) husbandman's cabbage.]</ety> <def>A
brassicaceous plant of many varieties, cultivated for its leaves, which
are not formed into a compact head like the cabbage, but are loose, and
are generally curled or wrinkled; kale.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bored</ent>⟦br⟧
